, Rice and Vegetables","content":["14 oz jasmine rice","35 oz water","24 oz chicken thighs, skinless, boneless, cut into pieces (1¼ in.-1½ in.)","3 ½ oz carrots, cut into thin strips","3 ½ oz broccolini, cut into thirds","3 ½ oz cauliflower, cut into small florets (1¼ in.)","2 oz red bell pepper, cut into thin strips","2 oz yellow onion, cut into thin wedges","3 oz sugar snap peas, trimmed and cut into halves"]}],"id":"r106910","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-MxXBlPMV89Y\/XZQvqBaE2QI\/AAAAAAAAceM\/_V6zGlh_wQcdwQUse_0wXYBiHURBNy9xACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_JvVF6CkMD4iB0Izg.png","title":"Easy Satay Chicken","publishedAt":"2017-03-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25.8 g","fat":"31.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"62.3 g","calories":"2689 kJ \/ 640 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["Try making your own peanut butter to use in this recipe. Please refer to The Basic Cookbook for the Peanut Butter recipe.","To save time buy pre-cut vegetables at the store.","Serrano chili can be replaced with Thai red chili when available."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","1h","6 portions"]}